oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Talk of Europe - The debates of the European Parliament as Linked Open Data
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Hollink, Dr L.H. (CWI)
Aggelen, MSc A.V.A. van (VU University Amsterdam)
Beunders, Prof H.B. (Erasmus University Rotterdam)
Kleppe, Dr M.K. (VU University Amsterdam)
Kemman, MSc M.K. (University of Luxembourg)
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: European Parliament
Linked Open Data
Open Government Data
multilingual data
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The Talk of Europe (TOE) project has curated the proceedings of the European Parliament (EP) from 1999 onwards, including all available translations in other EU languages, and converted these to RDF. Moreover, the data are enriched with biographical and political information on the speakers. Since the data are available in multilingual form, this dataset lends itself to be linked with resources in other European countries, such as parliamentary records or news reports.
oai_dc:dc.dc:contributor: Giannini, MSc S.G. (Universit? degli studi di Bari Aldo Moro)
Funding Agency: Clarin ERIC and Clarin-NL.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: The verbatim reports of the plenary meetings of the EP, as found on the Europarl website via portal http://www.europarl.europa.eu/plenary/en/debates-video.html.
